OL,3,CWhich countries are paying athletes
OL,4,Cfor winning gold at the Olympics?
OL,6,FWinning gold at the Olympics is
OL,7,Fpriceless for athletes who have worked
OL,8,Fyears to get to the very top - but
OL,9,Fwhile some will be rewarded with a
OL,10,Fhefty cash prize, many can expect to
OL,11,Freceive almost nothing for their win.
OL,13,FCash bonuses vary at this year's games
OL,14,Fin Paris, with some countries paying
OL,15,Fathletes more than $100,000 (#78,000)
OL,16,Ffor topping the podium, and others
OL,17,Fopting to provide grants and benefits.
