OL,3,CWhich countries are paying athletes
OL,4,Cfor winning gold at the Olympics?
OL,6,FFifteen of those will pay more than
OL,7,F$100,000 (#78,000) to athletes who bag
OL,8,Fthe top prize.
OL,10,FHong Kong pays athletes an eyewatering
OL,11,F$768,000 (#766,000) for taking home
OL,12,Ffirst place.
OL,14,FIt also pays $380,000 (#295,500) to
OL,15,Fathletes who win a silver medal - more
OL,16,Fthan any of the 32 other nations will
OL,17,Fpay for Olympic glory.
OL,19,FHong Kong competes separately from
OL,20,Fmainland China at the games, and has
OL,21,Fdone so since 1952.
