OL,3,CWhich countries are paying athletes
OL,4,Cfor winning gold at the Olympics?
OL,6,FOf those who responded to Forbes,
OL,7,FIsrael came in second, awarding
OL,8,F$275,000 (#214,000) to winning
OL,9,Fathletes, with Serbia in third at
OL,10,F$218,000 (#169,800).
OL,12,FThe United States, which is sitting at
OL,13,Fthe top of the leaderboard for all
OL,14,Fmedals won at the Paris Games at the
OL,15,Ftime of writing, offers less than
OL,16,F$40,000 to athletes who make it to the
OL,17,Fpodium.
OL,19,FEvery US athlete who wins gold will be
OL,20,Fawarded $37,500 (#29,300), courtesy of
OL,21,Fthe US Olympic & Paralympic Committee.
