OL,3,CWhich countries are paying athletes
OL,4,Cfor winning gold at the Olympics?
OL,6,FThose who have a definite shot at a
OL,7,Fmedal can receive up to #28,000 in
OL,8,Ffunding each year, which contributes
OL,9,Fto their living and sporting costs.
OL,11,FThis means the likes of GB's Tom
OL,12,FPidcock, Nathan Hales and Alex Yee,
OL,13,Fwho all took home gold for their
OL,14,Fcountry, will not receive a cash bonus.
OL,16,FBritish Athletics, the governing body
OL,17,Ffor the nation's track and field team,
OL,18,Fdoes reportedly pay out medal bonuses
OL,19,Findependent of the government.
